South African White, Yellow Corn, Wheat Prices Gain by Maximum Daily Limit

-- B y   M k h u l u l i   M a n c o t y w a
-- 
2011-03-18T07:13:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/south-african-white-yellow-corn-wheat-prices-gain-by-maximum-daily-limit.html
South African corn and wheat prices
rose by their maximum daily limits on the South African Futures
Exchange.  White corn for July delivery, the most active contract on
the exchange, rose as much as 80 rand, or 5.3 percent, to 1,595
rand a metric ton and was trading at 1,592 rand a ton as of 9:10
a.m. in Johannesburg. Yellow corn also increased by its daily
limit of 80 rand to 1,649 rand a ton and was last trading at
1,646 rand. Wheat gained 100 rand, or 3.3 percent, to 3,095
rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mkhululi Mancotywa in Johannesburg at 
 mmancotywa1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  